{"lemma":"ضَوْء","slug":"ضَوْء","root":"ض.#.#","root_slug":"ض-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26136","n26137"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%A1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَاءَ (ḍāʔa, “to shine”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"light","examples":[{"text":"عِنْدَمَا تَنْطَفِئُ الْأَضْوَاء، يُمْكِنُنَا رُؤْيَة النُّجُوم بِوُضُوح.","english":"When the lights go out, we can see the stars clearly."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/dˤawʔ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26136","headword_ar":"ضَوْءٌ","root":"DwA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duwo'N","text_ar":"ضُوْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyaA='N","text_ar":"ضِيَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiwaA='N","text_ar":"ضِوَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) the last of which is [erroneously] written in the L"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DawaA='N","text_ar":"ضَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) signify the same, (S, M, O, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) accord. to the leading lexicologists; but see what follows: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dawo'N","text_ar":"ضَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaA='a","text_ar":"ضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O, Msb, K,) and so is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duwo'N","text_ar":"ضُوْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) or this is a simple subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaA='a","text_ar":"ضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyaA='N","text_ar":"ضِيَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is also, sometimes, written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Diy^aA='N","text_ar":"ضِيَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDaA='a","text_ar":"اَضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaA='a","text_ar":"ضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dawo'N","text_ar":"ضَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duwo'N","text_ar":"ضُوْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDowaA='N","text_ar":"اَضْوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyaA='N","text_ar":"ضِيَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes a pl., (M, TA,) as Zj states it to be: (TA:) some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dawo'N","text_ar":"ضَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a more intensive signification than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that hence God has likened his direction [the Kur-án] to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uwr","text_ar":"النُّور"},{"kind":"text","text":"rather than to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~awo'","text_ar":"الضَّوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because if it were otherwise, no one had erred: and that hence, also, [in the Kur x. 5,] the sun is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyaA='","text_ar":"ضِيَا=ء","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the moon,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is also said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dawo'N","text_ar":"ضَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rays that are diffused by what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the kádee Zekereeyà affirms that these two words are syn. by their original application, but that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dawo'N","text_ar":"ضَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more forcible accord. to usage: and some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~awo'u","text_ar":"الضَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which subsists by itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as [that of] the sun, and fire; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uwru","text_ar":"النُّورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to that which subsists by some other thing [as does the light of the moon]. (MF, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","O","K","TA","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n26137","headword_ar":"ضُوْءٌ","root":"DwA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, in three places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}